In lesson 4 of ChatGPT Prompt Engineering for Developers, Andrew Ng and Isa Fulford discuss how large language models can be used to summarise text, particularly in e-commerce websites with high volumes of reviews. They demonstrate how to modify the prompts to extract relevant information and generate short summaries for specific departments, such as shipping or pricing. A for loop example is also provided, showing how summarising multiple reviews can aid in building efficient dashboards.